 IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.
    PROGRAM-ID. STRINGHANDLE.
    DATA DIVISION.
      WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.
      01 WS-CNT1 PIC 9(2) VALUE 0.
      01 WS-CNT2 PIC 9(2) VALUE 0.
      01 WS-STRING PIC X(25) VALUE 'ABCDADADADABVDFDFFAF'.
      01 WS-STRING-DEST PIC A(30).
      01 WS-STR1 PIC A(15) VALUE 'COBOL'.
      01 WS-STR2 PIC A(7) VALUE 'EXEMPLO'.
      01 WS-STR3 PIC A(9) VALUE 'DE TAMBEM'.
      01 WS-COUNT PIC 99 VALUE 1.
      01 WS-UNSTR PIC A(30) VALUE 'EXEMPLO DE COBOL'.
    PROCEDURE DIVISION.
      *> contar o número de caracteres na String, guardar em ws-cnt1
      INSPECT WS-STRING TALLYING WS-CNT1 FOR ALL WS-STRING CHARACTERS .
      DISPLAY "WS-CNT1 : "WS-CNT1.

      *> contar somente o caracter A
      INSPECT WS-STRING TALLYING WS-CNT2 FOR ALL 'A'.
      DISPLAY "WS-CNT2 : "WS-CNT2.

      *> substituir o caracter A por X na string
      DISPLAY "OLD STRING : "WS-STRING.
      INSPECT WS-STRING REPLACING ALL 'A' BY 'X'.
      DISPLAY "NEW STRING : "WS-STRING.

      *> Concatenação de String
      STRING WS-STR2 DELIMITED BY SIZE
        WS-STR3 DELIMITED BY SPACE
        WS-STR1 DELIMITED BY SIZE
        INTO WS-STRING-DEST
        WITH POINTER WS-COUNT
        ON OVERFLOW DISPLAY 'OVERFLOW!'
      END-STRING.
      DISPLAY 'WS-STRING : 'WS-STRING-DEST.
      DISPLAY 'WS-COUNT : 'WS-COUNT.

      *> Quebra de String
      UNSTRING WS-UNSTR DELIMITED BY SPACE
        INTO WS-STR3, WS-STR2, WS-STR1
      END-UNSTRING.
      DISPLAY 'WS-STR1 : 'WS-STR1.
      DISPLAY 'WS-STR2 : 'WS-STR2.
      DISPLAY 'WS-STR3 : 'WS-STR3.

    STOP RUN.

